note: Title from introduction (p. 5); alternate title from p. [1].

msContents.summary: Jaghmīnī's treatise on astronomy and geography with a preface and dedication to Ulugh Beg on the first 5 pages. Includes many diagrams and some empty spaces left for illustrations that were never completed.

supportDesc.extent: 67 paginated leaves : 220 x 130 (170 x 90 and 170 x 75) mm
supportDesc.foliation: Pages are numbered in ink, upper center: [1]-134. References in the record are to page numbers as they appear in the manuscript.

layoutDesc.layout: 14-23 long lines with extensive marginalia, including interlinear comments.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoNote: Two tables (p. 12-13) and 45 diagrams in red and black; headings and other finding aids also in red.

decoNote.#text: Diagram: planets of the Solar System
Diagram: orbits of Venus, Earth's moon, and Mercury

binding.p: Covers missing, unsupported sewn textblock with helical style primary endband.

origin.p: Not dated; text was dedicated to Ulugh Beg when first composed; a marginal note on p. 2 also gives a date of A.H. 1256 (1840).
